            "title": "Virco Mfg. Corporation reports $92.1 million in shipments, $15.4 million operating income for Q2 despite revenue reduction.",
            "id": "6e261571-d819-4446-94e1-476099efa91f",
            "description": "In Torrance, California on September 5, 2025, Virco Mfg. Corporation (NASDAQ: VIRC), a top manufacturer and direct supplier of moveable furniture and equipment for educational settings and public areas in the United States, announced robust profitability for the Second Quarter and the initial six months concluding on July 31, 2025, despite a general decline in demand for educational furniture and equipment. Shipments for the Second Quarter amounted to $92.1 million, a decrease from $108.4 million for the same quarter in the previous year. Operating income for the quarter stood at $15.4 million, down from $21.9 million recorded last year.",
